data.title: 10 Best Horror Films of 1967
data.meta_description:
The strong run that has been the 60's shows no signs of slowing here with yet another really good crop of horror.  With rare exception, it is interesting to note that black and white horror has essentially vanished by this point.  It marks the end of a visual form tied to virtually all of the classics of horror's early days.

Notable Films sometimes labelled as horror: Marat/Sade, Games, Titicut Follies, Weekend

Notable Films that didn't make the cut: Django Kill...If You Live Shoot!, Torture Garden, The Shuttered Room, The Torture Chamber of Dr. Sadism, Night of the Big Heat, The Living Corpse, It!, The Bloody Dead, The Spirit Is Willing, Doctor Faustus, Berserk, Succubus, The Image, The Mummy's Shroud, The Gruesome Twosome, The Vengeance of Fu Manchu, Theatre of Death, King Kong Escapes, Son of Godzilla, They Came from Beyond Space, The X from Outer Space, Something Weird, Yongary, A Taste of Blood, Gappa the Triphibian Monster, Gamera vs. Gaos, Hillbillys in a Haunted House
